{{Infobox person | name = Alexander Mirtchev | occupation = Economist, Academic, Author | education = LLM, [[George Washington University]], Ph.D., St. Kliment Ohridski University | image = | caption = Alexander Mirtchev }}
'''Alexander Vassilev Mirtchev''' ([[Bulgarian language|Bulgarian]]: Александър Василев Мирчев) (April 28, 1957)<ref>http://astanaforum.org/2014/en/author/alexander-mirtchev</ref> is an economist, academic, macroeconomic advisor and author.<ref name = "KrullCorp">{{cite web|url=http://www.krullcorp.com/en/dr-alexander-mirtchev.html |title=Krull Corporation - Dr. Alexander Mirtchev|accessdate=23 July 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://video.cnbc.com/gallery/?play=1&video=3000197755|title=Why the G20 was very 'productive'|publisher=[[CNBC]]|date=September 9, 2013}}</ref> He is a former fellow at the [[Woodrow Wilson International Center for Scholars]],<ref name="Wilson Center">{{cite web|url= http://www.wilsoncenter.org/staff/alexander-mirtchev |title=Wilson Center|accessdate=23 July 2013 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120505113848/http://www.wilsoncenter.org/staff/alexander-mirtchev |archivedate=May 5, 2012 |dead-url=yes}}</ref> Executive Chairman of [[Royal United Services Institute for Defence and Security Studies]] (RUSI) International<ref name="Rusi">{{cite web|url=http://www.rusi.org/about/council/ |title=RUSI Council |accessdate=23 July 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130806064410/http://www.rusi.org/about/council/ |archivedate=6 August 2013 }}</ref> and president and founder of Krull Corp. USA.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.krullcorp.com/en/about.html |title=Krull/About Us}}</ref>
==Early life and education== Mirtchev is an American<ref>{{cite court |litigants =Hourani v Mirtchev |vol =Lexis/Nexis LEXIS 65665, *20 (D.D.C. May 2013) |reporter =United States Courts Opinions |opinion = Judge Thomas F. Hogan |court =United States District Court District of Columbia |date = May 2013 |url=http://www.gpo.gov/fdsys/granule/USCOURTS-dcd-1_10-cv-01618/USCOURTS-dcd-1_10-cv-01618-1/content-detail.html }}</ref> born in [[Sofia]], [[Bulgaria]]. He earned an LLM degree in international and comparative law from [[George Washington University]] and a PhD from [[St. Kliment Ohridski University of Sofia|St. Kliment Ohridski University]] (also known as [[Sofia University]]). In addition, he studied [[economics]] and finance at the [[London School of Economics]] and Political Science at [[Boston University]] as well as [[Harvard Business School]].<ref name = "KrullCorp"/>
==Academic career== Mirtchev is an academic and has served as a fellow and member of numerous universities and educational institutions, including his role as American Founding Council Member of the [[Kissinger Institute on China and the United States]]. In addition, he has served as a Senior Fellow of the Russian and [[Bulgarian Academy of Sciences]], as Doctor Emeritus of the University of Foreign Trade and Finance, Ukraine, and as a member of the [[Russian Academy of Natural Sciences]].<ref name="Wilson Center"/>{{failed verification|date=June 2016}}
==Professional career== Alexander Mirtchev is Executive Chairman of the [[Royal United Services Institute|Royal United Services Institute for Defense and Security Studies International]] (RUSI) and Vice President of the [[Royal United Services Institute]] for Defence and Security Studies (RUSI), London.<ref name = "Rusi"/> He is also the president of Krull Corp. USA.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.krullcorp.com/en/dr-alexander-mirtchev.html |title=Dr. Alexander Mirtchev}}</ref> He is a Board Director and Member of the Executive Committee of the [[Atlantic Council]] of the [[United States]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.acus.org/users/alexander-mirtchev |title=Atlantic Council of the United States}}</ref> and was a member of the Wilson National Cabinet at the [[Woodrow Wilson International Center for Scholars]].<ref name="Wilson Center"/>{{failed verification|date=June 2016}} He serves as an independent member of the advisory board of Washington & Jefferson College's Center for Energy Policy and Management,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.washjeff.edu/news/president-krull-corp-appointed-wj%E2%80%99s-center-energy-policy-and-management-advisory-board|title=President of Krull Corp. Appointed to W&J's Center for Energy Policy and Management Advisory Board}}</ref> independent director of the sovereign wealth fund [[Samruk-Kazyna]]<ref name="Reuters1">{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2009/08/18/us-markets-sovereign-joint-idUSTRE57H3C820090818| title=Sovereign funds join forces for strategic investment | work=Reuters | date=18 August 2009}}</ref> and has served as director of the Law Offices of Stewart & Stewart.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.stewartlaw.com/Article/AllPublications |title=Steward and Stewart All Publications}}</ref>
==Media and Publications== Mirtchev has appeared as an economics analyst by [[BBC News]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.freenewspos.com/english/video/world%20economy/dfR_V6jAGEo|title=Alexander Mirtchev and Haruhiko Kuroda on BBC World News on Japan's Economy|date=April 16, 2013|publisher=BBC News|accessdate=16 July 2013}}</ref> [[Reuters]], [[Bloomberg L.P.|Bloomberg]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qGwQuYiQoXo |title=Bloomberg Interview with Alexander Mirtchev}}</ref> European Energy Review, [[CNBC]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7sb9QK1ib6s|title=CNBC - G8 Summit's Overarching but Limited Policy Output|publisher=CNBC|accessdate=16 July 2013}}</ref> [[Al Jazeera English]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aljazeera.com/programmes/rizkhan/2010/05/20105910144957657.html|title=The Impact of Greece's Downturn|last=Khan|first=Riz|date=May 11, 2010|publisher=Al Jazeera English|accessdate=16 July 2013}}</ref> [[Voice of America]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailymotion.com/video/xzhtyn_dr-alexander-mirtchev-of-krull-corp-discusses-emerging-markets-with-voice-of-america_news#.UeVtXVOjj8N|title=Economic and Financial Crisis in Emerging Markets|publisher=Voice of America|accessdate=16 July 2013}}</ref> E&ETV,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qlQZChSu6SE&list=PL1701616FF2D4C3F5&index=1|title=Russia-Ukraine Gas Dispute|publisher=E&ETV|accessdate=16 July 2013}}</ref> Focus Washington,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tMOpsh-ree4 |title=Focus Washington: Alexander Mirtchev}}</ref> The Globalist, Europe's World, and RealClearWorld, among other publications and television news programs. He is the author of a number of articles and has served as editor and publisher of a range of academic and professional journals. He also co-authored the Atlantic Council of the United States/RUSL report "Global Perspectives on Europe's Strategic Future."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.acus.org/event/global-perspectives-europes-strategic-future|title=Global Perspectives on Europe's Strategic Future|date=December 4, 2012|publisher=Atlantic Council of the United States|accessdate=16 July 2013}}</ref> Mirtchev wrote the introduction to the Russian-language edition of [[Lee Kuan Yew]]'s memoirs, ''From Third World to First, The Singapore Story, 1965-2000'', while the forward to the book was written by Henry Kissinger.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Third-World-First-Singapore-1965-2000/dp/0060197765|title=From Third World to First: The Singapore Story}}</ref> Mirtchev is presently a [[Forbes]] contributor and often writes about alternative energy technologies.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/investor/2012/08/27/alternative-energy-and-global-energy-security-in-aftermath-of-rio20/2/|title=Alternative Energy and Global Security in the Aftermath of Rio+20 | work=Forbes | first=Alexander|last=Mirtchev}}</ref>
