'''Dargaite''' is a rare mineral with formula BaCa<sub>12</sub>(SiO<sub>4</sub>)<sub>4</sub>(SO<sub>4</sub>)<sub>2</sub>O<sub>3</sub>. It is the [[barium]]-analogue of [[nabimusaite]], also differing from it in the lack of fluorine. It is one of many recently approved new minerals coming from the [[Hatrurim]] complex. Dargaite, as nabimusaite, is trigonal (space group ''R''-3''m'').<ref>: Gfeller, F., Galuskina, I.O., Galuskin, E.V., Armbruster, T., Vapnik, Y., Dulski, M., Gardocki, M., Jeżak, L., and Murashko, M., 2015. Dargaite, IMA 2015-068. CNMNC Newsletter No. 28, December 2015, 1860; Mineralogical Magazine 79, 1859–1864</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mindat.org/min-46885.htmll |title=Dargaite: Dargaite mineral information and data |website=Mindat.org |accessdate=2016-03-02}}</ref>
