'''Justus Ludwig Adolf Roth''' (September 15, 1818, [[Hamburg]] – April 1, 1892) was a [[Germany|German]] [[geologist]] and [[mineralogist]].
==Biography== In 1844 he obtained his doctorate from the [[University of Jena]] and spent the next few years working as a [[pharmacist]] in Hamburg. In 1848 he relocated to Berlin, where he came under the influence of [[Gustav Rose]] and [[Heinrich Ernst Beyrich]]. In 1867 he became an associate professor of [[mineralogy]] at the [[Humboldt University of Berlin|University of Berlin]].<ref name=HS>[http://www.deutsche-biographie.de/sfz77091.html Roth, Justus] Deutsche Biographie</ref>
He may be regarded as one of the founders of [[petrography|petrographical science]]. In his published papers he dealt with [[metamorphism]] and crystalline [[schist]]s, discussed the origin of [[Serpentine group|serpentine]], and wrote on the rocks of [[Mount Vesuvius]] and [[Ponza Island]].<ref>{{Cite EB1911|wstitle=Roth, Justus Ludwig Adolf}}</ref>
== Selected works == His separate works included: *''Der Vesuv und die Umgebung von Neapel'' (1857) &ndash; On [[Vesuvius]] and the environs of [[Naples]]. *''Die Gesteinanalysen in tabellarischer Übersicht und mit kritischen Erläuterungen'' (1861) &ndash; Rock analyzes in tabular overview with critical explanations. *''Beiträge zur Petrographie der plutonischen Gesteine'', a continuation of the preceding work (1869, 1873, 1879, 1884) &ndash; Contributions to the petrography of [[plutonic rock]]s. *''Flußwasser, Meerwasser, Steinsalz'' (1878) &ndash; River water, [[sea water]] and [[rock salt]]. *''Allgemeine und chemische Geologie'' (3 volumes, 1879–93) &ndash; General and [[chemical geology]]. *''Die geologische Bildung der norddeutschen Ebene'' (1879) &ndash; The geological formation of the [[North German plain]].<ref name=HS/> *''Über die Erdbeben'' (1882) &ndash; About the earthquake.
