'''''Spiroplasma mirum''''' is a [[bacteria|bacterium]] in the genus [[Spiroplasma]]. A strain of it, called ''Spiroplasma mirum'' strain SMCA (Suckling mouse cataract agent), causes cataracts in suckling mice.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ijs.microbiologyresearch.org/content/journal/ijsem/10.1099/00207713-32-1-92?crawler=true&mimetype=application/pdf|title=Spiroplasma mirum, a New Species from the Rabbit Tick (Haemaphysalis leporispalustris)|publisher=microbiologypublisher.org|accessdate=November 18, 2015}}</ref>
